WEBVTT

00:08.300 --> 00:10.302
♪ ♪

00:37.246 --> 00:39.248
[indistinct chatter]

00:44.545 --> 00:46.630
[Lee] Irene, I'm bored.

00:46.714 --> 00:48.424
You said you wanted to go out.

00:48.507 --> 00:50.634
Here we are. Out.

00:50.718 --> 00:53.345
[Lee] I said go out
and have a good time.

00:53.429 --> 00:56.182
And maybe talk to some boys?

00:56.265 --> 00:58.559
I don't have the patience.

00:58.642 --> 00:59.769
[Tom] All right.

00:59.852 --> 01:01.270
Huh? What did I miss?

01:01.353 --> 01:03.439
Well, I bet Franklin 25 bucks
he couldn't run the table on me.

01:03.522 --> 01:05.858
Yikes. Okay, where is Franklin?

01:05.941 --> 01:07.443
Hey, Franklin, your shot.

01:07.526 --> 01:09.111
[Franklin] Yeah, just a sec.

01:09.195 --> 01:11.363
- They mixed it all around.
- [Tom] Hey, come on, man.

01:11.447 --> 01:13.115
These guys are waiting.

01:13.199 --> 01:15.117
[coins clattering]

01:16.535 --> 01:18.496
Well, nice of you to join us.

01:18.579 --> 01:21.832
Ooh. Table still looks terrible.

01:21.916 --> 01:24.126
- Mm-hmm.
- Chin up, Randy. I could miss.

01:24.210 --> 01:26.462
[Randy] What do I need
money for anyway?

01:26.545 --> 01:28.088
[Tom] They don't have beer
in Saigon?

01:28.172 --> 01:29.924
[laughter]

01:41.644 --> 01:43.521
Yeah, I am gonna
miss you, buddy.

01:43.604 --> 01:47.650
But at least I'll have 25 bucks
to remember you by.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.985
[Randy chuckles]

01:58.786 --> 02:00.120
[laughter]

02:00.204 --> 02:01.789
Good game.

02:02.998 --> 02:05.417
Excuse me, gents.

02:15.094 --> 02:16.303
Lucky shot.

02:16.387 --> 02:19.098
[Irene] You hit it this way
on purpose.

02:19.181 --> 02:22.142
Yes. Yeah. [laughs]

02:22.226 --> 02:25.020
Well, what are the odds that
you'd be sitting in this seat?

02:25.104 --> 02:29.316
That is the silliest thing
that anyone has ever said to me.

02:29.400 --> 02:32.152
[♪ Elvis Presley: "I Want You,
I Need You, I Love You"]

02:33.696 --> 02:36.198
Say...

02:36.282 --> 02:38.617
you like Elvis Presley songs?

02:38.701 --> 02:42.246
Elvis? Isn't he a bit
over the hill?

02:42.329 --> 02:44.582
You'll come around.

02:44.665 --> 02:46.083
Is that right?

02:46.166 --> 02:48.711
♪ From the start ♪

02:48.794 --> 02:51.547
♪ I want you, I need you ♪

02:51.630 --> 02:54.466
♪ I love you ♪

02:54.550 --> 02:59.305
♪ With all my heart ♪♪

03:01.348 --> 03:04.143
Son of a swineherd.

03:07.229 --> 03:10.774
Sweetheart, I think it's time
to trade me in on a newer model.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.694
- [laughs softly]
- I left the silverware

03:13.777 --> 03:15.070
in the thing again.

03:15.154 --> 03:17.281
- Uh-oh.
- Should we still eat it?

03:17.364 --> 03:18.490
Oh, why not?

03:18.574 --> 03:20.284
Let's live dangerously.

03:20.367 --> 03:21.994
[laughs softly]

03:24.204 --> 03:26.165
Please don't use so much salt.

03:26.248 --> 03:28.626
What? I thought we were
living dangerously.

03:28.709 --> 03:30.377
You heard what the doctor said.

03:30.461 --> 03:32.254
And don't say "What?"

03:33.756 --> 03:36.717
You know, they told me not
to marry an English teacher,

03:36.800 --> 03:39.637
but I went and done it anyways.

03:46.644 --> 03:48.062
You all right?

03:49.146 --> 03:51.523
Yeah, I-I'm just
not very hungry.

03:53.567 --> 03:57.112
Well, you haven't had enough
to keep a bird alive.

03:57.196 --> 03:59.740
- You need to eat, hon.
- [salt shaking]

04:04.662 --> 04:06.956
Easy fix. Just a loose gasket.

04:07.039 --> 04:10.542
Shouldn't make
that noise anymore.

04:10.626 --> 04:13.295
How about we go see
the stars tonight?

04:13.379 --> 04:14.588
Again?

04:14.672 --> 04:16.757
It feels like we just went.

04:16.840 --> 04:20.135
Really? Oh, let's go.

04:20.219 --> 04:22.221
Please?

04:28.102 --> 04:30.437
[Irene] You're sure
you don't mind?

04:30.521 --> 04:33.565
[Franklin] No, I'm fine.

04:59.842 --> 05:01.844
♪ ♪

05:13.647 --> 05:16.025
Remind me to change
that bulb, will you?

05:16.108 --> 05:18.777
[grunts]

05:18.861 --> 05:21.739
Oh, and gas up the car.

05:24.533 --> 05:30.289
And the, uh, the ice cream
with the, uh... malt balls.

05:30.372 --> 05:35.335
Light bulbs, gas...

05:35.419 --> 05:37.963
Okay, I got you.

05:46.597 --> 05:48.599
There we go.
[grunts]

05:52.561 --> 05:55.564
- You all right?
- Yeah. Fine.

05:55.647 --> 05:57.399
Here.

05:57.483 --> 05:59.318
Just rest a second.

06:04.698 --> 06:05.824
[cap clicks]

06:05.908 --> 06:08.494
[Franklin] Hold your horses.

06:34.311 --> 06:36.313
[scraping]

06:50.160 --> 06:52.621
- You don't trust me?
- Take the bowl.

06:54.623 --> 06:56.750
You ready to make history?

06:56.834 --> 06:58.418
You say that every time.

06:58.502 --> 07:00.129
It still applies.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.775
♪ ♪

07:43.297 --> 07:44.506
[Franklin exhales]

07:46.508 --> 07:47.634
See?

07:47.718 --> 07:50.721
I don't always... [gags]

07:52.806 --> 07:54.016
[coughs]

07:55.642 --> 07:57.394
[lid clacks]

07:57.477 --> 08:00.105
It's just 'cause you
said something.

08:01.773 --> 08:03.775
[whirring]

08:06.737 --> 08:08.739
♪ ♪

08:31.428 --> 08:33.430
♪ ♪

08:55.202 --> 08:58.330
I love you, Irene.

08:58.413 --> 09:00.249
I love you too, Franklin.

09:11.593 --> 09:13.595
♪ ♪

09:34.032 --> 09:35.784
How's it looking
out there tonight?

09:35.867 --> 09:37.202
Anything interesting?

09:37.286 --> 09:41.456
Oh, it's-it's always
interesting to me.

09:41.540 --> 09:42.791
I know it is.

09:45.085 --> 09:46.336
You ready to head back soon?

09:46.420 --> 09:48.547
The game's on.

09:48.630 --> 09:51.967
Oh, you go on back.
I'm gonna stay a bit.

09:52.050 --> 09:55.762
Well, I'm not gonna leave
you here all by yourself.

09:55.846 --> 09:58.348
Okay, just, uh...

09:58.432 --> 10:01.184
give me a few minutes, then.

10:04.021 --> 10:05.397
Is something going on with you?

10:05.480 --> 10:08.984
You've been wanting to come
out here more and more.

10:10.736 --> 10:13.238
- That's not true.
- Yes, it is.

10:13.322 --> 10:15.157
Ever since last year.

10:15.240 --> 10:17.701
Since after you fell.

10:20.871 --> 10:23.665
Well, it's always good
to get out of the house.

10:23.749 --> 10:26.460
[laughs]

10:26.543 --> 10:27.919
Most people want to get out
of the house,

10:28.003 --> 10:31.173
they go to dinner,
maybe a movie.

10:31.256 --> 10:33.967
Most people don't have this.

10:34.051 --> 10:36.303
[Franklin] Yep.

10:40.682 --> 10:42.809
Something's different, though.

10:42.893 --> 10:45.729
You're thinking about this
even when we're not out here.

10:45.812 --> 10:48.440
Oh, now you're reading my mind?

10:48.523 --> 10:50.859
Yeah. Well, I've known you
for a little while now.

10:50.942 --> 10:53.487
- I'm-I'm getting there.
- What's your point, Franklin?

10:53.570 --> 10:55.989
I-I just...

10:56.073 --> 10:59.576
I mean, don't you...

10:59.659 --> 11:02.245
Aren't you getting a little bit
tired of this?

11:02.329 --> 11:03.538
'Cause I am.

11:04.873 --> 11:05.916
No.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.709
I'm not.

11:09.711 --> 11:11.171
Look.

11:11.254 --> 11:14.132
Yeah, yeah, I get
it's a heck of a view.

11:14.216 --> 11:16.635
Oh, it's more than that.

11:16.718 --> 11:18.261
Is it?

11:21.181 --> 11:24.518
856 times

11:24.601 --> 11:28.146
we've made
this trip, now, and...

11:28.230 --> 11:31.608
nothing's happened.

11:31.691 --> 11:33.902
We sit here,
we look out the window.

11:35.987 --> 11:38.949
That's all there is.

11:39.032 --> 11:42.327
I'm pretty sure that's
all there ever will be.

11:44.704 --> 11:47.165
What about the door?

11:47.249 --> 11:48.375
[stammers]

11:48.458 --> 11:49.793
Sweetheart,
you saw what happened

11:49.876 --> 11:51.211
when I put the mice out there.

11:51.294 --> 11:52.754
They didn't last a minute.

11:52.838 --> 11:55.549
Well, then, we'll...

11:55.632 --> 11:59.928
we'll just have to wait.

12:00.011 --> 12:03.056
Yeah? Wait for what?

12:03.140 --> 12:05.809
We're not getting any younger.

12:07.936 --> 12:11.773
I think these trips
are starting to take a toll.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.612
We can't keep
doing this forever.

12:20.907 --> 12:24.077
Maybe it's time we...

12:24.161 --> 12:26.746
we finally tell somebody else.

12:26.830 --> 12:27.998
- Maybe Denise.
- No.

12:28.081 --> 12:31.501
This is the last thing
Denise needs.

12:31.585 --> 12:33.211
It'll just scare her.

12:34.838 --> 12:36.715
[exhales]

12:36.798 --> 12:41.052
There's a reason we were
the ones who found this.

12:41.136 --> 12:43.138
It was meant for us.

12:43.221 --> 12:46.224
This is our riddle to solve.

12:46.308 --> 12:50.312
Don't take that away from me.

12:51.646 --> 12:53.482
Of course not.

12:57.861 --> 12:59.571
[Irene exhales]

13:12.459 --> 13:13.877
[shushes]

13:18.840 --> 13:20.675
- [whimpers]
- [shushes]

13:20.759 --> 13:21.968
[whispering] Sit.

13:23.970 --> 13:25.180
Good girl.

13:28.266 --> 13:30.644
[Franklin] Well, that was
a pretty decent workout.

13:33.772 --> 13:36.233
I might sleep down here tonight.

13:36.316 --> 13:39.361
The other mattress.
My back's a little mad at me.

13:42.906 --> 13:44.991
I'll be fine.

13:45.075 --> 13:48.245
Don't worry. Just a night or two
here, I'll be good as new.

13:50.455 --> 13:53.166
Watch the rest of the ball game.

13:53.250 --> 13:55.252
Sweet dreams, hon.

13:58.755 --> 14:00.590
[sportscaster] Taken a little
low and outside.

14:00.674 --> 14:02.676
And that'll run it...

14:02.759 --> 14:05.512
[whirring]

14:08.640 --> 14:10.141
[sighs]

14:16.815 --> 14:20.402
[TV playing indistinctly
in distance]

14:20.485 --> 14:23.488
♪ ♪

14:41.881 --> 14:43.883
♪ ♪

14:50.015 --> 14:52.142
[thunder rumbling]

15:07.782 --> 15:09.784
♪ ♪

15:23.798 --> 15:26.092
What are you gonna do
while I'm at the doctor?

15:26.176 --> 15:28.094
Well, I got some errands to run.

15:31.556 --> 15:33.683
Why don't you do something fun?

15:33.767 --> 15:36.186
When was the last time
you saw Randy?

15:36.269 --> 15:38.438
Oh, I don't think
I'm built for that anymore.

15:38.521 --> 15:40.732
You know I fall asleep
after one beer.

15:40.815 --> 15:43.109
- You do.
- Want to trade?

15:44.402 --> 15:47.489
No. I have enough
of my own, thanks.

15:50.200 --> 15:52.202
[engine starts]

15:59.584 --> 16:02.170
[Franklin] Ugh.
Look at that guy.

16:03.546 --> 16:04.756
[horn honking]

16:13.765 --> 16:17.143
- Unbelievable.
- [Irene] Oh, he's just trying

16:17.227 --> 16:19.896
to be helpful, Franklin.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.940
[Bryon] [laughs] Hey, you two.

16:22.023 --> 16:23.358
What are you doing?

16:23.441 --> 16:24.901
Oh, I just had the mower out.

16:24.984 --> 16:27.070
I just figured I'd give
your side a little trim.

16:27.153 --> 16:30.365
- Hope you don't mind.
- Thank you for taking
the time, Byron.

16:30.448 --> 16:32.409
You really didn't have to.

16:32.492 --> 16:34.452
Don't mention it.
You know, I'm a simple man.

16:34.536 --> 16:36.454
I see grass, I mow it.

16:36.538 --> 16:38.164
- See a property line,
you trespass it.
- Oh...

16:38.248 --> 16:40.500
[laughs]

16:40.583 --> 16:42.335
I'm innocent, I swear.

16:42.419 --> 16:44.504
I wanted it mowed,
I'd do it myself.

16:44.587 --> 16:47.257
[stammers] Hey, we could,
um, do a tool swap.

16:47.340 --> 16:50.009
You know, I sure could use
that planer of yours

16:50.093 --> 16:51.803
- if it's available.
- Planer's broken.

16:51.886 --> 16:54.305
Well, maybe
when it's back in action?

16:58.143 --> 17:00.603
- [Irene] Good to see you.
- Yeah, you, too.

17:14.492 --> 17:16.077
Uh, lunch is in the fridge.

17:16.161 --> 17:18.705
It's just half a salad,
so don't get too excited.

17:18.788 --> 17:20.707
Well, it does have bacon in it.

17:20.790 --> 17:22.834
Hey, uh, I've been
texting with this woman

17:22.917 --> 17:24.919
that I met at the gym last week,
and she said

17:25.003 --> 17:27.005
that there's a bowling league
here that we can join.

17:27.088 --> 17:28.423
What do you think?

17:28.506 --> 17:30.383
Time for the Banana Splitters
to ride again?

17:30.467 --> 17:32.594
That Franklin York is a liar.

17:32.677 --> 17:35.972
Hon, please, not this again.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.641
He said his planer was broken,

17:38.725 --> 17:42.061
but I saw fresh-planed wood
right by his workshop.

17:42.145 --> 17:44.731
Hey, what is your obsession?

17:44.814 --> 17:48.443
Okay, you're gonna laugh,

17:48.526 --> 17:51.738
but I think they're hiding
something in that shed.

17:51.821 --> 17:54.199
[grunts softly] Look,

17:54.282 --> 17:55.992
I found the granddaughter
on Facebook

17:56.075 --> 17:58.745
and I sent her a message
telling her what you saw.

17:58.828 --> 18:00.914
- What?
- It is their problem, not ours.

18:00.997 --> 18:04.000
Hey, we've only been here
for six months. Leave them be.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.127
For my sake.

18:06.211 --> 18:07.921
You don't have the best history
with neighbors,

18:08.004 --> 18:10.673
and I would like to keep
getting invited to things.

18:10.757 --> 18:12.759
[sighs]

18:16.971 --> 18:20.892
Did you want the Wilpons' tree
to fall on our house?

18:20.975 --> 18:23.102
[scoffs]

18:24.312 --> 18:26.356
[horn honks]

18:30.902 --> 18:33.112
[music playing softly]

18:33.196 --> 18:35.323
You could be nicer to him.

18:35.406 --> 18:37.325
Who, Byron?

18:37.408 --> 18:39.744
No, thanks.

18:39.828 --> 18:41.371
Well...

18:41.454 --> 18:44.582
Maybe if you gave him a chance,
you two could be friends.

18:44.666 --> 18:47.627
The guy gives me the willies.

18:47.710 --> 18:49.671
You know he lets the dog
sleep in bed with him?

18:49.754 --> 18:52.632
Oh, for heaven's sakes,
Franklin, he likes animals.

18:52.715 --> 18:54.676
It's his marriage bed.

18:54.759 --> 18:57.178
[laughs] I cannot...

18:57.262 --> 18:59.013
You are so stubborn.

19:00.932 --> 19:03.476
What is going on with you?

19:03.560 --> 19:07.063
Trying to get me
to make friends with Byron.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.941
Telling me to go to the pool
hall in the middle of the day.

19:10.024 --> 19:14.487
I just think it would be nice
if you got out and were social.

19:14.571 --> 19:16.906
It keeps you sharp.

19:16.990 --> 19:18.741
I don't want to see
other people.

19:18.825 --> 19:23.246
Well, I don't want to feel like
all you do is take care of me.

19:23.329 --> 19:25.331
♪ ♪

19:51.107 --> 19:53.401
[exhales]

19:55.320 --> 19:57.488
Yours must be as hard as mine.

19:58.489 --> 20:00.992
Hey, there. Sorry for the delay.

20:01.075 --> 20:03.912
- Irene, you can come back now.
- [laughs] Thank you.

20:03.995 --> 20:06.331
We've got a few scans and tests
to run this afternoon.

20:06.414 --> 20:09.042
It's all routine,
but it might take a little bit.

20:09.125 --> 20:11.044
I-I'll call you
when I'm finished.

20:11.127 --> 20:12.754
How's the back, Mr. York?

20:12.837 --> 20:15.715
Oh, you know, good days and bad.
Can't complain.

20:15.798 --> 20:17.175
Well, it is a doctor's office.

20:17.258 --> 20:20.094
Complaining is encouraged.

20:20.178 --> 20:22.347
Oh, don't forget the ice cream.

20:22.430 --> 20:23.848
Yes, ma'am.

20:29.062 --> 20:30.897
Have a nice day.

20:32.482 --> 20:34.400
[Mareese] You haven't come
to see me for months.

20:34.484 --> 20:37.028
I assumed it was because
you were improving.

20:37.111 --> 20:38.446
Am I not?

20:38.529 --> 20:40.949
I see you're still in the chair.

20:41.032 --> 20:44.077
Well, only when I leave home.

20:44.160 --> 20:46.496
Trying to be extra cautious.

20:46.579 --> 20:48.623
And how often
are you leaving home?

20:48.706 --> 20:50.333
Are you eating? Exercising?

20:50.416 --> 20:51.834
Did you finish your appointments

20:51.918 --> 20:53.670
- with the physical therapist?
- [laughs] What is this,

20:53.753 --> 20:56.464
some sort of inquisition?

20:56.547 --> 20:58.675
Look, I won't sugarcoat this.

20:58.758 --> 21:00.760
I'm concerned.

21:00.843 --> 21:03.012
You shouldn't be
in this condition at 73,

21:03.096 --> 21:04.430
even after the fall.

21:04.514 --> 21:07.266
You're making this sound worse
than it is, Sandra.

21:07.350 --> 21:10.311
- I'm fine.
- I'm sorry,
but you're not fine.

21:10.395 --> 21:12.397
I think you know that.

21:12.480 --> 21:14.732
Is there anything in your life
that might be contributing

21:14.816 --> 21:16.317
to these symptoms?

21:19.487 --> 21:22.448
Not that I can think of, no.

21:23.658 --> 21:25.785
Irene, some of the things
you're experiencing

21:25.868 --> 21:27.578
are often made worse
by depression.

21:27.662 --> 21:30.498
I am not depressed.

21:32.000 --> 21:33.918
Well, I want to run
some more tests.

21:34.002 --> 21:36.295
We should up the benazepril
for your blood pressure.

21:36.379 --> 21:38.923
Levothyroxine as well.

21:39.007 --> 21:40.800
[fading] You need
a scheduled nutrition program

21:40.883 --> 21:42.260
and supplements.

21:42.343 --> 21:45.263
For the headaches
and insomnia, doxepin.

21:45.346 --> 21:48.307
P.T. More frequent checkups.

21:48.391 --> 21:51.185
[voice continues fading]

21:58.317 --> 22:02.113
[distant] Have you considered
in-home care?

22:02.196 --> 22:03.656
Irene?

22:03.740 --> 22:06.409
Have you considered
in-home care?

22:08.619 --> 22:11.706
Oh, uh, Franklin
can take care of me.

22:13.708 --> 22:17.628
I'm not sure he's up
for that. Not anymore.

22:27.346 --> 22:29.766
[clerk] Do you have
a Rewards Card?

22:29.849 --> 22:33.936
Uh, somewhere. Yeah.

22:34.020 --> 22:35.438
Oh, sorry.

22:35.521 --> 22:38.399
- [phone ringing]
- Hang on, just a sec.

22:39.817 --> 22:41.736
- Hi, Denise? Can I...
- [Denise] Hey, Grandpa.

22:41.819 --> 22:43.696
Can I call you back?
I'm at the store right now.

22:43.780 --> 22:46.991
Guess what? I'm coming to town.

22:47.075 --> 22:49.702
I'm actually driving in
right now.

22:49.786 --> 22:51.662
Oh. Right now?

22:51.746 --> 22:54.916
Hey, maybe let
someone else go, huh, Pop?

22:54.999 --> 22:56.834
Just meet me at Jelinek's, okay?

22:56.918 --> 22:59.087
J-- Okay, all right, goodbye.

22:59.170 --> 23:00.296
[sighs]

23:00.379 --> 23:02.799
- Finished?
- Yeah. Now I am, yeah.

23:02.882 --> 23:06.636
Let me just, uh,
get that Rewards Card.

23:07.720 --> 23:09.222
Somewhere.

23:24.654 --> 23:27.281
- Hey, Grandpa.
- Hi, Princess.

23:27.365 --> 23:28.574
[Denise grunts]

23:30.284 --> 23:33.287
- Where's Nana?
- She's at the doctor.

23:33.371 --> 23:35.540
- Just a checkup.
- Are you sure?

23:35.623 --> 23:37.291
She looked a little bit frail
the last time I saw her, so...

23:37.375 --> 23:39.961
She's fine, she's just,
you know...

23:40.044 --> 23:42.338
- How about a piece of cake?
- Of course.

23:46.050 --> 23:47.969
- [phone beeps]
- [Franklin] Hi, this Franklin.

23:48.052 --> 23:51.013
I'm not available right now, but
if you leave me a message and...

23:54.183 --> 23:56.561
[exhales] I-I'm sure
he'll be here soon.

23:56.644 --> 23:57.937
Okay.

23:58.020 --> 24:00.690
Irene, please don't
disappear again.

24:00.773 --> 24:02.650
You can't ignore this.

24:02.733 --> 24:04.819
A-Apparently not.

24:11.659 --> 24:13.911
How's your mom?

24:13.995 --> 24:15.872
Good. She and Trevor just had

24:15.955 --> 24:17.790
their ten-year
wedding anniversary.

24:17.874 --> 24:19.458
- Ten years?
- Mm-hmm.

24:19.542 --> 24:21.502
Hmm.

24:21.586 --> 24:23.671
Yeah, how about you?

24:23.754 --> 24:25.590
How's school treating you?

24:27.508 --> 24:29.135
School is great.

24:29.218 --> 24:31.345
Internship is great.

24:34.348 --> 24:36.642
- Sweetie?
- What?

24:36.726 --> 24:39.312
You want to tell me
what's bothering you so much

24:39.395 --> 24:41.314
you're taking it out
on that poor napkin?

24:41.397 --> 24:42.690
Oh.

24:42.773 --> 24:44.650
[laughs softly]

24:44.734 --> 24:47.570
Uh, promise you won't be mad?

24:47.653 --> 24:51.199
Well, no, I mean, wh...
You okay?

24:51.282 --> 24:53.201
Yeah, I'm fine.

24:53.284 --> 24:55.119
Uh...

24:56.329 --> 24:58.289
I got a...

24:58.372 --> 25:01.083
I got a message this morning.

25:02.168 --> 25:04.462
Well, what kind of message?

25:04.545 --> 25:07.048
One of your neighbors
found me on Facebook

25:07.131 --> 25:09.300
- and said that they...
- [chuckles] Oh, Facebook.

25:09.383 --> 25:11.636
Was it Jim Denn--
Is Dennings on Facebook?

25:11.719 --> 25:13.262
It doesn't matter who.

25:13.346 --> 25:18.434
What-what matters is they
were walking their dog, and...

25:18.517 --> 25:22.605
they saw you pushing Nana around
in the middle of the night.

25:25.024 --> 25:27.485
Is that it?

25:27.568 --> 25:34.116
I mean, you know how Nana
likes to take the night air.

25:34.200 --> 25:35.660
That's what you're
worried about?

25:35.743 --> 25:38.329
Yeah, I am. And...

25:40.331 --> 25:44.043
I think you two should consider
moving out of the house.

25:48.798 --> 25:52.468
Because we took a walk?

25:52.551 --> 25:53.886
No, it's not just that.

25:53.970 --> 25:56.347
I've been thinking about this
since Nana fell.

25:56.430 --> 26:01.894
Well, that was last year,
and she's... she's doing better.

26:04.313 --> 26:06.399
She could have died.

26:11.862 --> 26:14.615
[exhales]

26:14.699 --> 26:18.411
I know this might be hard
to understand, Princess, but...

26:21.998 --> 26:25.167
...we're just gonna stick
where we are.

26:25.251 --> 26:29.088
And if that means I keel over
dead walking up the stairs

26:29.171 --> 26:30.756
or-or pruning the roses

26:30.840 --> 26:33.634
or wheeling your Nana around
all hours of the night,

26:33.718 --> 26:35.886
well, then, so be it.

26:35.970 --> 26:38.973
- But it doesn't make sense...
- Denise, I-I said no.

26:44.061 --> 26:45.479
[exhales]

26:48.941 --> 26:50.943
[phone keys clicking]

27:00.661 --> 27:02.204
- Excuse me?
- Jesus.

27:02.288 --> 27:03.873
I forgot you were here.

27:03.956 --> 27:05.916
When my husband arrives,
will you let him know

27:06.000 --> 27:08.085
that I've gone across the street
to visit an old friend?

27:08.169 --> 27:09.837
Sure.

27:09.920 --> 27:11.547
Thank you.

27:13.174 --> 27:15.176
[indistinct chatter]

27:29.482 --> 27:31.734
Miss Boyle,
what are you doing out here?

27:31.817 --> 27:34.028
May I ask what you're doing?

27:34.111 --> 27:35.988
- Let's get you back
to your room.
- Hey!

27:36.072 --> 27:38.991
What? I'm just taking
Miss Boy...

27:39.075 --> 27:41.118
- I'm so sorry.
- [Irene] It's fine.

27:41.202 --> 27:42.536
This is Irene York.

27:42.620 --> 27:44.872
And as far as I know,
she doesn't live here.

27:47.458 --> 27:49.001
It's fine.

27:53.672 --> 27:56.509
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

27:56.592 --> 27:58.677
Sorry, but do I know you?

27:58.761 --> 28:00.513
It's Chandra.

28:00.596 --> 28:02.056
Yeah, I was
one of your students.

28:02.139 --> 28:05.601
I-I wrote my final paper
on the Brontë sisters,

28:05.684 --> 28:07.019
and you said it was
one of the best...

28:07.103 --> 28:10.481
- [laughs] Oh. Yes.
- [chuckles]

28:10.564 --> 28:12.983
- Chandra.
- Yeah. Are you thinking

28:13.067 --> 28:16.028
- about moving in?
- Oh, no. I-I...

28:16.112 --> 28:18.948
I was just hoping to see
my friend Sadie Norton.

28:19.031 --> 28:22.576
Oh, of course.
Did you know George?

28:22.660 --> 28:26.539
Mm. I did see his obituary
in the paper.

28:26.622 --> 28:29.667
Well, I could take you
to her room. May I?

28:29.750 --> 28:31.752
Oh, yes. Thank you.

28:33.754 --> 28:35.714
[Chandra] They were really
in love, those two.

28:35.798 --> 28:37.967
But he was pretty gone
by the end.

28:38.050 --> 28:39.802
Didn't even recognize her.

28:39.885 --> 28:43.431
After 60 years, just like that.

28:43.514 --> 28:45.558
So, how are you doing,
Mrs. York?

28:45.641 --> 28:47.852
- You still teaching?
- Oh, no.

28:47.935 --> 28:50.896
I-I retired some time back.

28:51.939 --> 28:54.066
[Chandra] You were a really
important teacher for me.

28:55.359 --> 28:56.944
I even majored in English.

28:57.027 --> 28:59.947
Yeah, I thought I'd be
a teacher too. Just like you.

29:00.030 --> 29:02.199
Didn't work out.

29:02.283 --> 29:04.410
Well, this is a good job.

29:04.493 --> 29:06.036
You're-you're helping people.

29:06.120 --> 29:08.080
This job, it is tough.

29:08.164 --> 29:09.498
You know, I know
you still got it together,

29:09.582 --> 29:12.084
but the truth is,
most of the people in here,

29:12.168 --> 29:13.878
they don't know
what they want or need,

29:13.961 --> 29:16.797
and they don't appreciate
what you do for them.

29:16.881 --> 29:19.175
Well, look at me,
I'm just blabbering again.

29:19.258 --> 29:22.261
- We are at Sadie's room.
- [exhales]

29:22.344 --> 29:23.971
Well, I don't want to keep you.

29:24.054 --> 29:25.848
I know you have
a lot of work to do.

29:26.891 --> 29:28.642
Right. Of course.

29:28.726 --> 29:30.811
Well, it was nice to see you
again, Mrs. York.

29:30.895 --> 29:34.315
And, uh, who knows, maybe
you'll move in here someday.

29:34.398 --> 29:36.692
We always have new spaces
opening up.

29:45.034 --> 29:47.036
[door creaks]

30:08.015 --> 30:10.351
Are you here to fix the window?

30:10.434 --> 30:13.729
No, Sadie, it's Irene.

30:13.812 --> 30:16.148
Irene York.

30:16.232 --> 30:17.983
Irene.

30:19.068 --> 30:20.444
Is that really you?

30:20.528 --> 30:23.072
[laughs] Oh, yes.

30:23.155 --> 30:25.491
It's been a long time.

30:26.575 --> 30:28.869
Are you okay here?

30:28.953 --> 30:31.830
[laughs] I have my friend.

30:31.914 --> 30:33.958
[both laugh]

30:34.041 --> 30:37.962
Did I tell you I used to own
a bridal shop?

30:38.045 --> 30:41.090
I would sew all the veils.

30:41.173 --> 30:45.553
Look, you can see where I
pricked myself with the needle.

30:45.636 --> 30:48.430
Oh, I know, The Lovely Bride.

30:48.514 --> 30:50.849
I worked there one summer,
remember?

30:50.933 --> 30:52.351
Irene.

30:54.353 --> 30:57.314
Irene, is that really you?

30:57.398 --> 30:58.524
Yes.

30:58.607 --> 31:02.611
You had the most
incredible hair.

31:02.695 --> 31:06.073
You used to tie
all that ribbon in it.

31:06.156 --> 31:08.367
- I was so jealous of that.
- [both laugh]

31:08.450 --> 31:10.452
You made me pay
for all that ribbon.

31:10.536 --> 31:12.663
- It was a lot of ribbon!
- [both laugh]

31:12.746 --> 31:14.623
Yes, it was.

31:16.208 --> 31:17.960
Ah...

31:18.961 --> 31:21.964
Are you here to fix the window?

31:22.047 --> 31:24.133
No, no.

31:24.216 --> 31:26.760
Sadie, I came to see you.

31:26.844 --> 31:30.264
I was so sorry
to hear about George.

31:30.347 --> 31:34.435
I came here to see
how you were doing.

31:34.518 --> 31:38.606
I thought maybe you needed
a visit from an old friend.

31:38.689 --> 31:40.107
Oh.

31:40.190 --> 31:42.276
We weren't friends.

31:42.359 --> 31:45.362
Yes, uh, Irene.

31:45.446 --> 31:48.949
- I worked at the...
- I know who you are, Irene.

31:49.033 --> 31:51.160
We were never friends.

31:51.243 --> 31:53.954
You weren't
a very good employee.

31:54.038 --> 31:56.707
[laughs softly] You...

31:56.790 --> 32:00.002
you always thought
you were very smart,

32:00.085 --> 32:05.132
but actually,
y-you were quite silly.

32:05.215 --> 32:09.762
Have I told you
I used to own a bridal shop?

32:09.845 --> 32:11.055
[stammers]

32:23.942 --> 32:26.236
I have something
to tell you, Sadie,

32:26.320 --> 32:28.238
and you're very lucky,

32:28.322 --> 32:32.951
because I've never told anyone
this in my whole life.

32:36.330 --> 32:38.540
I've been somewhere.

32:38.624 --> 32:41.627
Somewhere far, far from here.

32:41.710 --> 32:43.253
Very far.

32:43.337 --> 32:49.009
Farther than any human
has ever gone, by light-years.

32:49.093 --> 32:52.638
Oh, I've seen miraculous things.

32:52.721 --> 32:57.393
I'm special, Sadie.

32:57.476 --> 33:02.189
I'm the most special person
you've ever met in your life.

33:04.900 --> 33:07.319
But now...

33:07.403 --> 33:10.030
I'm sick.

33:12.032 --> 33:13.659
And I'm scared.

33:13.742 --> 33:15.703
And I...

33:15.786 --> 33:18.664
I'm not so sure anymore.

33:25.379 --> 33:28.882
Are you here to fix the window?

33:39.727 --> 33:41.478
Hey, hey!

33:51.572 --> 33:53.073
Irene?

34:00.998 --> 34:03.667
[sighs] Sweetheart, I'm home!

34:09.923 --> 34:11.341
God.

34:19.099 --> 34:21.018
[brakes squeak]

34:39.411 --> 34:41.747
Do you want to talk about it?

34:42.998 --> 34:45.584
I can take care of myself.

34:46.668 --> 34:49.213
But it's not just yourself.

34:49.296 --> 34:51.924
You have to take care of me,
too.

34:53.175 --> 34:54.927
And that's not fair.

34:55.010 --> 34:57.137
Well, now you're...

34:57.221 --> 34:58.806
twisting it like it's a burden.

34:58.889 --> 35:00.015
That's...

35:00.098 --> 35:02.100
You sound just like Denise.

35:02.184 --> 35:04.061
- Denise?
- Yeah, I saw her today.

35:04.144 --> 35:06.855
That's-that's why I got
so darn distracted.

35:07.898 --> 35:09.566
She thinks we're getting senile
or something.

35:09.650 --> 35:12.402
She... wants us to move.

35:13.487 --> 35:15.489
♪ ♪

35:18.826 --> 35:20.160
Do you want to?

35:21.411 --> 35:22.329
Want to what?

35:22.412 --> 35:23.747
Move.

35:24.832 --> 35:26.208
[exhales]

35:28.210 --> 35:30.546
Well, you said it yourself
last night.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.173
We can't keep doing this
forever.

35:34.216 --> 35:36.218
[alert beeping]

35:39.096 --> 35:40.430
- [groans]
- [buzzing]

35:40.514 --> 35:42.057
Sheep-dip.

35:43.058 --> 35:45.811
[sighs] I forgot to get gas.

35:45.894 --> 35:47.896
[engine sputtering]

35:51.233 --> 35:52.651
[engine turns off]

35:55.821 --> 35:58.031
Your, uh, your gauge
not working right now?

35:58.115 --> 36:00.784
No, it... it's me.

36:01.952 --> 36:03.787
[man] Got to pay attention
to these things, man.

36:03.871 --> 36:05.455
Especially at your age.

36:05.539 --> 36:07.583
[Franklin] Yeah,
it won't happen again.

36:08.667 --> 36:11.587
You don't have to report this
to anybody or anything, do you?

36:11.670 --> 36:14.047
[man] Nah. It's just gas.

36:14.131 --> 36:15.716
You'll be all right. I'll be
right back. Give me a second.

36:15.799 --> 36:17.718
Let me get your, uh, let me
get your signature real quick.

36:17.801 --> 36:19.428
[Franklin] Oh, yeah.

36:28.854 --> 36:31.398
[whispers] What do you want
from me?

36:31.481 --> 36:33.317
[thunder crashing]

36:43.452 --> 36:44.536
[grunts]

36:46.955 --> 36:48.916
- [keys jangle]
- [engine starts]

36:50.167 --> 36:52.711
All right, Mr. Nichols,
you are all booked,

36:52.794 --> 36:55.339
traveling August 13
from Knoxville to Dallas.

36:55.422 --> 36:58.717
Seat 11B. It's an aisle seat,
just like you wanted.

36:58.800 --> 37:00.594
Is there anything else
that I can help you with?

37:02.095 --> 37:03.639
Oh, that's very nice of you,
sir.

37:03.722 --> 37:06.308
Um, if you wouldn't mind
filling out a quick survey

37:06.391 --> 37:08.727
after the... Ah, son of a bitch.

37:08.810 --> 37:10.562
[scoffs] They always hang up,
huh?

37:10.646 --> 37:12.105
You know what, it's okay.

37:12.189 --> 37:13.857
I wouldn't want to fill out
a survey either.

37:13.941 --> 37:15.943
You almost done? I just want
to show you something.

37:16.985 --> 37:18.654
I'll be quick.

37:18.737 --> 37:19.780
How does...

37:19.863 --> 37:20.906
this look?

37:22.991 --> 37:23.909
Uh...

37:23.992 --> 37:26.119
"Albemarle"?

37:27.955 --> 37:29.790
How 'bout just "Byron"?

37:31.249 --> 37:33.001
You mean just...

37:33.085 --> 37:35.003
"Byron for Town Council"?

37:35.087 --> 37:36.880
Yeah.

37:36.964 --> 37:38.507
I like it.

37:38.590 --> 37:39.758
It's plain and simple.

37:39.841 --> 37:42.260
Oh! God, you always have
the best ideas.

37:42.344 --> 37:44.596
Hey, do-do you really need
signs?

37:46.264 --> 37:48.183
If I want to win,
I got to get my name out there.

37:48.266 --> 37:49.685
Yeah, but, uh...

37:49.768 --> 37:51.520
why not next year?

37:51.603 --> 37:54.147
Once we're
a little more settled.

37:55.148 --> 37:57.693
Look... [exhales]

37:57.776 --> 38:00.028
I never could've done this
back in Champaign.

38:00.112 --> 38:02.447
People there just... [grunts]

38:04.157 --> 38:06.284
...they didn't see me that way.

38:06.368 --> 38:07.953
But here?

38:08.036 --> 38:10.622
[chuckles softly] I can be...

38:12.040 --> 38:14.418
Councilman. [chuckles]

38:14.501 --> 38:16.253
You can be Mrs. Councilman.

38:16.336 --> 38:17.546
- Hmm?
- [chuckles softly]

38:18.588 --> 38:20.757
- [beeping]
- I have another call.

38:20.841 --> 38:22.926
- [whispers] Oh. Sorry.
- Uh, hi, this is Janine.

38:23.010 --> 38:25.012
How may I assist you
with your travels today?

38:26.972 --> 38:30.600
Uh, wonderful. And what dates
were you looking to fly?

38:31.727 --> 38:33.061
Okay.

38:33.145 --> 38:35.147
♪ ♪

38:38.567 --> 38:40.569
[crickets chirping]

38:43.238 --> 38:45.240
[Roxy panting]

38:50.454 --> 38:52.456
♪ ♪

38:54.750 --> 38:55.751
[grunts]

39:03.800 --> 39:05.260
[thumping]

39:08.013 --> 39:09.765
[creaking]

39:13.226 --> 39:15.228
♪ ♪

39:43.673 --> 39:44.633
[phone chimes]

39:44.716 --> 39:45.717
- [gasps, scoffs]
- [shattering]

39:52.432 --> 39:54.267
[sighs]

39:59.439 --> 40:01.024
[sighs]

40:04.820 --> 40:06.321
You know,

40:06.404 --> 40:09.074
when you asked me in the car

40:09.157 --> 40:10.283
if I wanted to move...

40:11.785 --> 40:13.411
...well...

40:14.830 --> 40:16.832
...honestly,
I've thought about it.

40:18.959 --> 40:21.294
'Cause of the stars.

40:22.337 --> 40:23.588
But, sometimes,

40:23.672 --> 40:25.423
looking at that...

40:25.507 --> 40:27.175
other sky...

40:30.345 --> 40:32.013
...it scares me.

40:35.433 --> 40:39.229
So I'd-I'd be lying if I said
I hadn't thought about it.

40:44.818 --> 40:46.319
But...

40:47.362 --> 40:49.614
...the end of the day, for me...

40:51.324 --> 40:53.160
...the answer is no.

40:56.037 --> 40:57.956
Just 'cause...

40:58.999 --> 41:01.334
...'cause I know
you don't want to.

41:04.129 --> 41:05.714
So I...

41:08.425 --> 41:10.719
So I don't want to either.

41:15.098 --> 41:16.349
Thank you.

41:21.229 --> 41:23.899
I went to see Sadie Norton
today.

41:23.982 --> 41:25.400
Yeah?

41:25.483 --> 41:26.985
[sighs]

41:27.068 --> 41:29.487
George passed away.

41:30.530 --> 41:32.240
[sighs]

41:34.743 --> 41:36.828
Franklin, we need to talk.

41:42.250 --> 41:44.669
What would you do if I died?

41:44.753 --> 41:46.463
Wait, what did the doctor say?

41:46.546 --> 41:47.797
This is not about the doctor.

41:47.881 --> 41:50.050
This is about you and me.

41:50.133 --> 41:52.135
What would you do?

41:58.183 --> 41:59.100
I'd die, too.

41:59.184 --> 42:00.810
Oh, come on, Franklin.

42:00.894 --> 42:02.729
- That's unacceptable.
- Well, I don't care

42:02.812 --> 42:03.939
what's acceptable.

42:04.022 --> 42:05.941
Well, I've thought about it,

42:06.024 --> 42:09.402
and I want you to promise me
that if I go first...

42:10.487 --> 42:11.988
...you'll sell the house.

42:12.072 --> 42:14.491
Move on. Just... [sighs]

42:14.574 --> 42:17.202
let somebody else
have a go at it.

42:21.539 --> 42:24.125
Well, what about our secret?

42:24.209 --> 42:26.127
Well,

42:26.211 --> 42:29.923
it'll have been our secret
long enough, don't you think?

42:32.217 --> 42:34.219
♪ ♪

42:39.557 --> 42:41.393
Okay.

42:41.476 --> 42:43.270
I promise.

42:47.274 --> 42:49.609
What's a good age, you think?

42:51.194 --> 42:52.946
For what?

42:53.029 --> 42:54.948
To live to.

42:55.031 --> 42:56.533
- Hundred?
- [chuckles]

42:56.616 --> 42:58.535
I'd be happy with that.

42:58.618 --> 43:00.161
[chuckles softly] Who wouldn't?

43:00.245 --> 43:01.663
[sniffs]

43:01.746 --> 43:05.750
Promise me you won't think
about dying until we're 100.

43:06.835 --> 43:07.919
Okay?

43:10.130 --> 43:12.132
'Cause I want those years.

43:15.260 --> 43:17.429
So just... [inhales]

43:20.015 --> 43:23.018
...just promise me, okay?

43:27.355 --> 43:29.107
I promise.

43:36.448 --> 43:39.284
♪ ♪

43:58.386 --> 44:00.305
Were you trying to protect me
from myself?

44:00.388 --> 44:03.475
[laughing]

44:03.558 --> 44:05.477
- [laughs]
- There... Come on.

44:05.560 --> 44:06.895
- I can't. [laughs]
- Quit squirming.

44:06.978 --> 44:08.313
You know you love this.

44:08.396 --> 44:10.815
It-it does feel good...

44:10.899 --> 44:14.444
[laughing] but it also tickles.

44:14.527 --> 44:16.029
Oh, my God.

44:16.112 --> 44:18.281
- So I should stop, I guess?
- No, no, don't stop.

44:18.365 --> 44:19.949
[laughing]

44:20.033 --> 44:21.785
