[snores softly]

47:30.056 --> 47:31.975
[Franklin snores softly]

47:34.394 --> 47:36.396
♪ ♪

47:59.669 --> 48:01.671
♪ ♪

48:07.885 --> 48:09.387
[sighs softly]

48:24.944 --> 48:27.697
[Irene] Dear Franklin,

48:27.780 --> 48:30.033
Let me first say...

48:30.116 --> 48:32.118
I'm sorry.

48:32.201 --> 48:34.871
I'm not doing this to hurt you.

48:34.954 --> 48:37.165
You know I would never.

48:37.248 --> 48:40.418
It's only that...

48:41.461 --> 48:44.922
...I've finished waiting. I...

48:45.006 --> 48:48.259
I've waited long enough.

48:50.303 --> 48:51.804
I'm ready.

48:53.765 --> 48:57.435
I know what's probably on the
other side of that door, but...

48:59.312 --> 49:01.314
...I have to see for myself.

49:05.068 --> 49:07.570
To make my own choice

49:07.654 --> 49:09.072
while I still can.

49:09.155 --> 49:11.157
♪ ♪

49:17.121 --> 49:21.125
Like so many times my own words
have failed me in life,

49:21.209 --> 49:24.045
I turn again to Auden.

49:24.128 --> 49:26.047
[crickets chirping]

49:26.130 --> 49:29.258
"How should we like it
were stars to burn

49:29.342 --> 49:32.345
With a passion for us
we could not return?"

49:32.428 --> 49:34.472
[creaking]

49:34.555 --> 49:36.891
"Admirer as I think I am

49:36.974 --> 49:39.560
Of stars that do not give a damn

49:39.644 --> 49:44.065
I cannot, now I see them, say

49:44.148 --> 49:48.152
I missed one terribly all day."

49:51.739 --> 49:55.660
"Were all stars
to disappear or die

49:55.743 --> 49:59.080
I should learn to look
at an empty sky

49:59.163 --> 50:02.917
And feel
its total dark sublime."

50:04.669 --> 50:06.671
♪ ♪

50:20.184 --> 50:22.437
Be strong.

50:22.520 --> 50:25.148
I know you can be.

50:26.149 --> 50:29.277
Tell Denise how proud I am.

50:30.611 --> 50:33.281
I'll give your love to Michael.

50:33.364 --> 50:35.491
And I'll see you again.

50:35.575 --> 50:37.326
I promise.

50:37.410 --> 50:39.162
All my love.

50:40.496 --> 50:42.081
Irene.

